  <!-- §9 What is a Kids Weighted Blanket? -->
  <h2>What is a Kids Weighted Blanket?</h2>
  <p>
    A weighted blanket is a specially designed throw or comforter filled with small beads (usually glass or plastic) that add evenly distributed weight. For kids, weighted blankets are typically 2–5 lbs—light enough to avoid safety hazards, but heavy enough to trigger deep pressure stimulation (DPS). This neurological response is similar to swaddling or a therapeutic hug: it activates the parasympathetic nervous system, reducing heart rate and cortisol, and promoting relaxation.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Yescool Kids Weighted Blanket uses a 7-layer construction with 3 lbs of glass beads locked in small pockets. This prevents bead migration and ensures even weight distribution across the entire 36x48-inch surface. The dual-sided design—minky dots on one side, cool microfiber on the other—adds versatility: warm for winter, cool for summer.
  </p>

  <!-- §10 Who Should Buy This? -->
  <h2>Who Should Buy the Yescool Kids Weighted Blanket?</h2>
  <h3>Buy If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Your child is 3+ years old and weighs 30–50 lbs.</li>
    <li>They experience anxiety, sensory sensitivities, or restless sleep.</li>
    <li>You want a reversible blanket that works year-round (minky + microfiber).</li>
    <li>You're willing to invest in quality construction and durability.</li>
    <li>Your child has ADHD, autism, or sensory processing differences that benefit from deep pressure.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Skip If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Your child is under 3 years old or under 20 lbs (safety risk).</li>
