    <li>
      <strong>Supervise and monitor comfort.</strong> Always ensure your child's face and neck are uncovered. Watch for signs of overheating (excessive sweating, flushed cheeks). Use the minky side in fall and winter for warmth; flip to the cool microfiber side in spring and summer. If your child doesn't enjoy the weight, respect their preference—this blanket isn't for every child.
    </li>
  </ol>

