  <!-- §15 FAQ Section -->
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Are weighted blankets safe for kids under 2?</summary>
      <p>
        No. Weighted blankets are not recommended for children under 2 years old or under 20 lbs due to suffocation and SIDS (Sudden Infant Death Syndrome) risk. The deep pressure from a weighted blanket can restrict breathing in very young children. The Yescool Kids Weighted Blanket is designed for ages 3+ and children weighing 30+ lbs. Always consult your pediatrician before introducing a weighted blanket to a young child.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>What happens if the fabric tears and glass beads spill out?</summary>
      <p>
        The Yescool blanket uses glass beads locked in small pockets, so they're unlikely to spill easily. However, if the outer fabric is damaged, glass beads could become a choking hazard or cause eye irritation if they come into contact with skin. Inspect the blanket regularly for tears or weak seams. If damage occurs, repair it immediately using needle and thread, or hand wash gently to prevent further deterioration. Consider hand washing over machine washing to extend the fabric's life and protect the seams.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Can the Yescool blanket be machine washed?</summary>
      <p>
        Yes, the Yescool blanket is machine washable according to the product specs. However, hand washing with gentle detergent and cold water is recommended to preserve the minky dots, microfiber softness, and bead pockets long-term. Machine washing, especially on hot settings or heavy cycles, can weaken seams and damage the fabric. If using a machine, use a gentle cycle, cold water, and consider placing the blanket in a mesh laundry bag for extra protection.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Why is the Yescool blanket $140 when cheaper options exist online?</summary>
      <p>
        Budget weighted blankets for kids on Amazon cost $25–40, so the $140 price tag is significant. The Yescool blanket costs more because of several premium features: (1) dual-sided design (minky + cool microfiber), eliminating the need for two blankets; (2) 7-layer construction for durability; (3) glass beads locked in small pockets for safety and even weight distribution; (4) reinforced seams and quality stitching. You're paying for versatility and longevity, not just weight. If budget is the priority, Amazon alternatives are viable. If durability and year-round use matter more, Yescool's premium justifies the investment.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Which side should I use—minky or microfiber?</summary>
      <p>
        Use the minky dot side in fall and winter for warmth and a plush, cozy texture. Switch to the cool microfiber side in spring and summer to prevent overheating while maintaining the gentle weighted pressure. The dual-sided design is the blanket's standout feature and allows you to adapt to temperature changes without buying two blankets. Some kids prefer one side over the other based on texture preference, so let your child experiment to find their favorite.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Does the Yescool blanket help kids sleep better?</summary>
      <p>
        Weighted blankets may reduce anxiety and improve sleep quality in some children, especially those with sensory sensitivities, ADHD, or autism. The deep pressure stimulation (DPS) mimics a calming hug, activating the parasympathetic nervous system and promoting relaxation. However, results vary by child. This blanket works best for kids who seek comfort and proprioceptive input. It's not a cure for clinical insomnia, sleep apnea, or diagnosed sleep disorders. If your child has a diagnosed sleep condition, consult a pediatrician before using a weighted blanket. For healthy kids with anxiety or restlessness, this blanket can be a helpful sleep aid.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>What weight should I choose for my child?</summary>
      <p>
        The rule of thumb is 10% of your child's body weight. For a 30-40 lb child, a 3-4 lb weighted blanket is appropriate. The Yescool Kids Weighted Blanket at 3 lbs is ideal for children 30-60 lbs. Avoid blankets heavier than 10% of body weight, as they may cause discomfort or safety concerns. If your child is at the edge of the weight range, start with the lighter option.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Will the blanket cause overheating in summer?</summary>
      <p>
        The cool microfiber side (on the Yescool's dual-sided design) is specifically chosen for warm seasons and helps prevent overheating. Its smooth, breathable material allows better airflow than typical weighted blankets. Pair with lightweight base sheets for maximum breathability. The blanket is NOT recommended for use in rooms consistently over 80°F.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Is this blanket big enough to share between siblings?</summary>
      <p>
        The Yescool Kids Weighted Blanket is approximately 48x40 inches. It's designed for a single child on a child-sized bed. For two children, it would be too small and wouldn't provide adequate weight distribution. Each child should have their own appropriately-weighted blanket for safety and comfort.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Does this blanket come with a removable cover?</summary>
      <p>
        No. The Yescool blanket does not have a removable cover — the minky and microfiber sides are sewn directly to the weighted core. This makes it more durable but means you must hand wash the entire blanket. Avoid submerging; hand wash gently in cool water with mild detergent and allow to air dry flat.
      </p>
    </details>
  </div>

